HEADWORD: magnetic mine
<hw>magnetic mine</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A marine
mine that is detonated by a mechanism that detects the nearness of
magnetic material (as the steel hull of a ship). A <stype>magnetic
counter mine</stype> may allow the passagw of several ships before
detonating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

